</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F3827FA6FFFC1A2DFF05CD6F4F43FCB7" pageId="2" pageNumber="566" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="BB272C2DFFFC1A2DFF05CD6F4F43FCB7" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="89ECF03FFFFC1A2DFF05CD6F4A2BFCD2" bold="true" box="[199,334,798,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="566">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in honor of Dra. Jocelia Grazia, distinguished Brazilian hemipterist, friend for many years and leading worker on 
<taxonomicName id="7C9857AEFFFC1A2DFD8ACD334985FCB6" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[584,736,834,860]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pentatomidae</taxonomicName>
with several seminal papers.
</paragraph>
